body:
I'd like opinions on this `$pmux` to `$shiftx` optimisation inside `proc_mux`
Doing so transforms the following circuit:
```
module top (CLK, SEL, SI, DO);
parameter SELWIDTH = 2;
parameter DATAWIDTH = 1;
input    CLK;
input [DATAWIDTH-1:0] SI;
input [SELWIDTH-1:0] SEL;
output [DATAWIDTH-1:0] DO;
localparam DATADEPTH = 2**SELWIDTH-1; // Note minus 1 so isn't a complete case
reg [DATAWIDTH-1:0] data [DATADEPTH-1:0];

generate
    genvar i;
    for (i = 0; i < DATADEPTH; i=i+1) begin
        always @(posedge CLK)
        begin
            if (i == 0)
                data[i] <= SI[i];
            else
                data[i] <= data[i-1];
        end
    end
    assign DO = data[SEL];
endgenerate
endmodule
```

from creating this on master @ ccfa2fe:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6740044/54873070-43d05e00-4d8c-11e9-87d9-d5fe9bbca9eb.png)

to creating this:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6740044/54873071-534fa700-4d8c-11e9-8137-8083e3adf942.png)

Are there any side effects to this?
The advantage is that this makes analysis much easier downstream...

